# FRONTEND IMPLEMENTATION SPECIFICATION

You are a senior frontend architect and SaaS product designer.

Your task is to build a complete production-ready React frontend for my project called:

AYD (Ask Your Database)

This is a DaaS (Database as a Service) platform centered around Hybrid Search.

You will receive the complete backend source code.

IMPORTANT RULES:

1. Create a new folder named FRONTEND.
2. Work ONLY inside the FRONTEND folder.
3. Do NOT modify, rename, delete, or refactor any backend files.
4. You must inspect the backend code and derive request/response structures directly from the implementation.
5. Use the existing backend API endpoints exactly as implemented.
6. If endpoint payload structures are unclear, infer them from the backend code.
7. Build the frontend to match the backend, not vice versa.

